modules.description: This module defines type representations for handling signed, unsigned, and unknown signedness integer types in OCaml. It provides abstract interfaces used to generate and manipulate C-compatible type signatures in PPX extensions. Concrete use cases include defining type layouts for foreign function interfaces (FFI) and ensuring correct type representation in generated code.

This module processes and generates OCaml code for interfacing with C by defining type representations and handling FFI declarations. It works with abstract syntax trees and type definitions to support code generation in PPX extensions. Concrete use cases include automating the creation of C bindings and ensuring type correctness in generated stubs.

Initializes runtime components required for integrating C stubs generated by `ppx_cstubs`. Works with C-compatible data types and OCaml foreign function interface (FFI) declarations. Use when embedding C functions directly into OCaml codebases that require custom stubs not handled by default tooling.
